This paper is about a neural narrative generation system that interacts with humans to generate stories. The paper discusses different levels of human interaction and their impact on story quality and human engagement. This work involves natural language processing, machine learning, and human-computer interaction, which are all relevant to the following arXiv CS sub-categories: cs.CL (Computation and Language), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction), and cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Among these, cs.CL and cs.AI are the most likely categories as they are directly related to natural language processing and machine learning, which are the core components of the proposed system.
